{
  "texts": [
    "Synthetic data in theorem proving.",
    "Synthetic data has long been recognized and used as an important ingredient in theorem proving [63] [64] [65] [66].",
    "State-of-the-art machine learning methods make use of expert iteration to generate a curriculum of synthetic proofs 2, 3, 15.",
    "Their methods, however, only generate synthetic proofs for a fixed set of predefined problems, designed and selected by humans.",
    "Our method, on the other hand, generates both synthetic problems and proofs entirely from scratch."
  ]
}